* [[JS8Call Rx]] - getting started

!260523

I set up JS8Call for the QMX+ by cloning the QDX profile.
Still using Kenwood TS-440S as the radio.
The audio routing was dead easy.
It just shows up as "QMX Transceiver" for both input and output.

CAT test passes.
PTT appears to pass.

When I hit "tune" in JS8Call the radio appears to be transmitting, although the power shown on the display is 0.0.
I see no power out on the ATU-10.
The speakers on the mac have a constant tone.

I checked the audio routing, and it all looks correct.

I see the mode is USB.
When I changed that to digi, tune briefly through out a 2.4W signal, then it dropped to 0.0 and mode switched to USB.
No tone on the speakers this time.

Fix: JS8Call / Preferences / Radio / Mode.
Change from USB to None.

The tone on mac speakers disappeared, and the radio is putting out ~3.1W now.
Progress.

Finally made a QSO, confirming JS8Call is working now.

(let's test transclusion)

